comments.body: Weinberg files for PRint Approval plan.  There is a one in the sandbox.  It loaded well.

The new approach is a hybrid approach.

For library credits, we will rely on the existing framework, where fine fee transactions with the fine/fee type of Credit will be exported via the Bursar transfer job in Alma.

For payment of library fines, the following process must be followed:
1. Circulation staff pay the fine with the payment method of 'Bursar Transfer'.
2. An Analytics report will run once a week to capture fine payments.
3. The output of the Analytics report will need to be translated into the format required for the bursar office.
Re-opening, as the new approach is a hybrid approach that will use the code written before.
